ipfs.title: Will twitter hide more than 2 tweets from the twitter account @realDonaldTrump before end of June?
ipfs.description:
Twitter has hidden one of Donald Trump’s tweets behind a warning that it “glorifies violence”, further escalating the social media company’s row with the US president.

The US president’s tweet, posted on Thursday night (28th of may) Washington time, warned people in Minneapolis protesting against the killing of a black man, George Floyd, by a white police officer that he would send the military to intervene if there was “any difficulty”.

“When the looting starts, the shooting starts,” Trump wrote, apparently quoting former the former Miami police chief Walter Headley, who in December 1967 promised violent reprisals to protests over stop-and-frisk tactics.

Two hours later, Twitter added a notice to the tweet: “This tweet violated the Twitter Rules about glorifying violence. However, Twitter has determined that it may be in the public’s interest for the tweet to remain accessible.” 

If twitter hides another tweet from @realDonaldTrump before end of June this market resolves as YES, otherwise it resolves as NO.
ipfs.resolution_description:
Resolution is based on twitter account @realDonaldTrump together with a common consensus based on multiple news sources such as CNN, BBC, CNBC and others. 

If the tweet is hidden for a limited time period it still counts and the market resolves as YES. 

If no more tweets are hidden the markets resolves as NO.

ipfs.title: Will the total death toll in the 2020 Twin city riots be above 15 before end of june ?
ipfs.description: The 2020 Twin Cities riots or 2020 Minneapolis riots are an ongoing series of civil disturbances in the Minneapolis–Saint Paul metropolitan area, Minnesota, United States. Unrest began in Minneapolis on May 26, after the death of George Floyd while being restrained by Derek Chauvin and other officers of the Minneapolis Police Department (MPD). Demonstrations and protests were initially peaceful, but windows were smashed at a police precinct, two stores were set on fire, and other stores were looted and damaged in the metropolitan area. Deaths are not uncommon in riots. If 15 people dies in this riot before 1st of July this market resolves as YES, otherwise NO. It do not matter if the person who dies is a protester, anti-protester, police, etc. Any death related to the riot counts.
ipfs.resolution_description:
The market resolution is based on common consensus from multiple news sites such as CNN, CNBC, BBC and more. 

If there are more than 15 deaths in the riots before end of june the market resolves as yes, otherwise it resolves as no.

ipfs.title: Will Binance Coin (BNB) price be above $15 by April 30th 23:59 2020 UTC?
ipfs.description: If Binance Coin (BNB) trades above $15.00 at the end of April UTC time (30th 23:59:59), this market will resolve as YES. This market will resolve as NO if the price is $15.00 or below. The price used will be the Coinmarketcap price found at https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/binance-coin/ If BNB trades at above $15.00 any time during the month but trades at $15.00 or below at the end of the month, this market will still resolve as NO.
ipfs.resolution_description: The market will use the Coinmarketcap price average found at https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/binance-coin/ The price used will be the average displayed price at the top of the page, not a particular exchange's price. The price used will be the price at the exact time of April 30th 23:59:59 UTC. The price must be above $15.00 for the market to resolve as YES. A price of $15.00 exact or lower will resolve as NO. The price at that exact time is used. If the price trades above $15.00 at any point before the end of April but below $15 at the end of the month, the market will still resolve as NO. The backup price used if Coinmarketcap data is unavailable will be the BNB:BTC trading pair found at https://www.binance.com/en/trade/BNB_BTC using Binance's own USD price conversion for BTC.
